</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="360" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="360">
<taxonomicName authority="Le Peletier &amp; Audinet-Serville, 1828" authorityName="Le Peletier &amp; Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1828" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Empria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Empria rubicola" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubicola">Empria rubicola</taxonomicName>
Ermolenko, 1971: 21-22. Type locality: Russia, Sakhalin Oblast, Novoaleksandrovsk. Holotype female, SIZ [examined].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="360" type="taxonomic affinities">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="360">Taxonomic affinities.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="360">
The closest species are 
<taxonomicName authority="Le Peletier &amp; Audinet-Serville, 1828" authorityName="Le Peletier &amp; Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1828" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Empria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Empria zhangi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhangi">Empria zhangi</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Le Peletier &amp; Audinet-Serville, 1828" authorityName="Le Peletier &amp; Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1828" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Empria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Empria quadrimaculata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrimaculata">Empria quadrimaculata</taxonomicName>
(see under 
<taxonomicName authority="Le Peletier &amp; Audinet-Serville, 1828" authorityName="Le Peletier &amp; Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1828" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Empria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Empria quadrimaculata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrimaculata">Empria quadrimaculata</taxonomicName>
Takeuchi, 1952 for details).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="360" type="host plants">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="360">Host plants.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="360">
Unknown. Holotype female and the studied paratypes (1 female, 2 males) were collected from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rubus idaeus" order="Rosales" pageId="13" pageNumber="360" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="idaeus">Rubus idaeus</taxonomicName>
L. subsp. melanolasius (Dieck) Focke(under the name 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rubus sachalinensis" order="Rosales" pageId="13" pageNumber="360" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sachalinensis">Rubus sachalinensis</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Ermolenko, VM" journalOrPublisher="Vestnik zoologii" pageId="17" pageNumber="364" pagination="18 - 24" title="Novye vidy i rod pililshchikov (Hymenoptera, Tenthredinidae) s ostrova Sakhalin. Soobshhenie I." volume="1971" year="1971">Ermolenko 1971</bibRefCitation>
), which is a common plant in Hokkaido.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="360" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="360">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="360">
East Palaearctic. Specimens studied are from Japan (Hokkaido) and Russia (Sakhalin Oblast). Most probably this species has to be removed from the list of Chinese species (
<bibRefCitation author="Yan, Y-C" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica" pageId="17" pageNumber="364" pagination="248 - 252" title="Two new species of Tenthredinidae (Hymenoptera, Tenthredinidae) from China." volume="34" year="2009">Yan et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
), because 
<taxonomicName authority="Le Peletier &amp; Audinet-Serville, 1828" authorityName="Le Peletier &amp; Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1828" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Empria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Empria rubicola" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubicola">Empria rubicola</taxonomicName>
has clypeus and upper half of the mesepisternum black (not yellow brown) and abdominal terga 2-4 (not 2-6) each with a pair of pale patches.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
